==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hellenism
<hw>Hel"len*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>Hell⟦eacute⟧nisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A phrase or form
of speech in accordance with genius and construction or idioms of the
Greek language; a Grecism.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The type of character of the ancient Greeks, who
aimed at culture, grace, and amenity, as the chief elements in human
well-being and perfection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hellenist</ent>⟦br⟧
